meanings.definition: To supply with an excessive amount.
meanings.sent1: The store oversupplied the shelves with too many products.
meanings.sent2: The farmer oversupplied the market with fresh vegetables.
meanings.sent3: The teacher oversupplied the students with homework, causing groans.
meanings.sent4: Her kindness oversupplied the community with warmth and support.
meanings.sent5: The rain oversupplied the fields with water, leading to flooding.

meanings.sent1: The oversupplied warehouse had no more space for new inventory.
meanings.sent2: The oversupplied buffet offered a wide variety of dishes.
meanings.sent3: His oversupplied closet burst at the seams with clothes.
meanings.sent4: The oversupplied market was bustling with options for shoppers.
meanings.sent5: The oversupplied pantry was filled to the brim with canned goods.
